The GPU node is reporting an XID error from NVIDIA driver, indicating a general GPU error.
These errors can stem from various sources, including hardware problems, NVIDIA software issues, or user application
problems.

### General Remediation

Many transient XID errors can be solved by simply rebooting the system or virtual machine instance. For more detailed
cases, check the documentation link below to find out about your specific error.

### NVIDIA XID Error Documentation

For detailed information about specific XID error codes and their meaning, refer to the official NVIDIA documentation:
[https://docs.nvidia.com/deploy/xid-errors/index.html](https://docs.nvidia.com/deploy/xid-errors/index.html)

### Common XID Error Categories

- **Hardware errors**: Check GPU temperature, power supply, and physical connections
- **Driver issues**: Ensure NVIDIA drivers are up to date and compatible with your GPU
- **Memory errors**: May indicate ECC memory issues or memory exhaustion
- **Application errors**: Check for CUDA programming errors or resource leaks